&quot;The truth is that Europe is embracing nuclear power.&quot;<br>
<br>
In fact, directly the opposite is true.<br>
<br>
ALL Western European nations have stopped building reactors.<br>
<br>
Countries are denuclearizing as a matter of law.&gt;&gt;&gt;<br>
<br>
They have stopped building reactors because they have enough. A handful of them are all that's required to meet all of France's energy needs. Your assertion that they are denuclearizing is just your opinion. A lull in construction does not translate to abandonment. If it was windmills we were talking about then construction would never finish. By the time you have built enough the first ones need replacing and more are needed to meet higher energy usage. With nuclear power it's easy to meet the demand. As can be clearly seen in France.<br>
Once they start building breeders construction will slow again. Energy will become too cheap and plentiful to warrant many more plants.<br>
<br>
