It uses neutrons from Pu or U fission to &quot;breed&quot;.<br>
<br>
It has some unique advantages and some disadvantages as compared with an Na-LMFBR.<br>
<br>
yale<br>
<br>
<br>
An interesting aside...<br>
<br>
Widespread use of MOX fuel (particularly, twice-thru or more) essentially forecloses creating a future breeder economy (assuming one would want to do such a thing).<br>
<br>
