&gt; electric is a pain in the arse because of the looooong<br>
&gt;downtime between charges...<br>
<br>
 Batteries are coming available which can drastically shorten that downtime. There are other ways too: any battery which isn't damaged by &quot;memory&quot; can be recharged anywhere you stop for a while. Work, home, visiting friends, whatever.<br>
 This would obviously be aided by recharge option at public places and best of all, a system for getting power from the grid, from transducers buried under roads -at least in special lanes on highways. The problem is that no place is willing to emplace the infrastructure for this, people don't see it as being available so they don't ask for it, so no place is willing to plant the systems - circular cycle, which leads people to think the option is useless.<br>
<br>
&gt; but then a hydrogen powered car would rely on oil for<br>
&gt;lubrication of moving engine parts too... so we're back<br>
&gt;to square one.<br>
<br>
Synthetics, Non-petrochemical formulations, and above all, not burning several liters per day, just to get from A-B. There's no possible way a car which can roll down the driveway under its own power can consume such vast amonts of hydrocarbons, just as lubricants. (holes shot through the combustion chambers, crappy seals &amp; valves, gasping lurching &amp; choking...)<br>
 Another interesting point: Propane is easy to convert a car to. Fuel is widely available, not too much modification, and none of it too exotic for the average owner. Running an engine which is only little modified from gasoline means the engine is a few degrees cooler most of the time. This means that demands on lubricants are much reduced, and a slight reduction in engine temperature means +25% or more to engine life.<br>
<br>
&gt; I would be interested to know how much fossil fuel<br>
&gt;is consumed at the utility plant to fully charge an<br>
&gt;electric car??? How much coal to the mile? <br>
<br>
 This is the worst argument about electrics ever.  Just try to build a vehicle which is as clean -amount of fuel burned for work accomplished- as a power plant. Minimum mass would be 20 tons, and 80% of that would be pollution control gear (WAG).<br>
 As dirty as fossil fuel power stations are, vehicles which run on dead dinosaurs are much _MUCH_ worse (there are things which can be done about this, but there aren't any cars on the road -certainly none offered by major auto makers- which significantly clean this up. How much do _you_ want to spend on clean air -from your own pockets &amp; habits? Typically, by most voters &amp; consumers, the answer is not much).<br>
 Every locality which gets most of its power from hydro should have strong programs to encourage electrics. How about areas served by nukes?<br>
<br>
yale wrote<br>
&gt;I agree hybrids have fantastic potential. The issue is<br>
&gt;the potential for grid connected straight electrics.<br>
<br>
 Transducers. (A lot like running trolley cars from overhead wires, but no wires, and the cars have battery capacity to run a good while off the grid.)<br>
 Another interesting one I heard of -I'll have to look for sources for it: At night, connect your car to a pump added to your house. It compresses methane fuel (&quot;Natural gas&quot; or household &quot;gas&quot;) into the car's tank for the next day. Supposedly, in most cases, it's cheaper for distance traveled. Probably better if you also use it through a series hybrid, charged from grid power at night. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/ujohnfraz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>John Fraz</A> at: 3/14/02 11:26:34 pm<br></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm8.showMessageRange?topicID=279.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a> <b>2</b> <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm8.showMessageRange?topicID=279.topic&start=41&stop=42>3</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm8.showPrevMessage?topicID=279.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm8.showNextMessage?topicID=279.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=279.topic&index=40><img src=http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/addreply3.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm8.emailToFriend?topicID=279.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm8.threadControl?topicID=279.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/space/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm8.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=279.topic><im